  "response": "While it is theoretically possible to fend off or even kill a wolf with bare hands, it is highly unlikely and extremely dangerous. Wolves are powerful predators with strong jaws and sharp teeth, and they are much larger and stronger than humans. If confronted by a wolf, the best course of action is to avoid confrontation, make yourself appear larger, make loud noises, and back away slowly. If attacked, your priority should be to protect yourself and escape rather than trying to fight back. It's always best to avoid situations where you might encounter a wolf in the wild.",
